you can actually get into orbit.

00:44:55.420 --> 00:44:57.140
And orbit means that
the dynamics here

00:44:57.140 --> 00:45:01.420
is such that you will actually
start circling this object.

00:45:01.420 --> 00:45:04.098
In fact, we never launch
spacecraft to stars.

00:45:04.098 --> 00:45:06.390
Typically, we launch them to
planets nearby, but then--

00:45:09.290 --> 00:45:12.970
So it turns out that
the trajectories

00:45:12.970 --> 00:45:16.410
that these spacecraft
follow, actually

00:45:16.410 --> 00:45:20.563
they also minimize their
"optical path," where there's

00:45:20.563 --> 00:45:21.730
no index of refraction then.

00:45:21.730 --> 00:45:23.050
It is just gravity.

00:45:23.050 --> 00:45:26.645
But they actually do follow the
minimum path around the star.

00:45:26.645 --> 00:45:29.020
And in fact, this has been
known for more than a century.

00:45:29.020 --> 00:45:32.290
I mean, Copernicus even
hinted at that in his work,

00:45:32.290 --> 00:45:40.450
when he computed the
orbits of the planets

00:45:40.450 --> 00:45:42.250
in the solar system.

00:45:42.250 --> 00:45:44.620
So these are very
well known stuff.

00:45:44.620 --> 00:45:47.982
So what I will do now, then,
is I will actually drive you,

00:45:47.982 --> 00:45:49.690
without really proving
anything, but that

00:45:49.690 --> 00:45:52.360
will drive you to a set
of Hamiltonian equations

00:45:52.360 --> 00:45:56.970
that describe the same
analogy, but for optics now.

00:45:56.970 --> 00:45:59.990
So in order to derive our
Hamiltonian equations,

00:45:59.990 --> 00:46:02.412
we actually need two postulates.

00:46:02.412 --> 00:46:03.870
Now what does it
mean, "postulate?"

00:46:03.870 --> 00:46:05.180
Do you know that word?

00:46:05.180 --> 00:46:07.434
Yes, [INAUDIBLE].

